-- Barcelona, Real Madrid Advance to Final of Spanish Soccer's  Copa de Rey
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2011-02-02T22:57:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-02/barcelona-real-madrid-advance-to-final-of-spanish-soccer-s-copa-de-rey.html
Barcelona and Real  Madrid  won to
advance to their first meeting in the final of Spanish soccer’s
Copa del Rey in 21 years.  Barcelona won 3-0 at Almeria to complete an 8-0 victory in
the two-match semifinal. Real Madrid beat defending champion
Sevilla 2-0 for a 3-0 series win. The final will be played April
20.  The teams last met for the title in 1990, with Barcelona
winning 2-0. Barcelona has won the Cup a record 25 times, while
Real’s 17 titles rank third.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  